    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you cast a spell that targets only one creature and doesn’t have a range of self, you can spend a number of sorcery points equal to 1 + the spell’s circle to target a second creature in range with the same spell. (Cantrips cost only 1 sorcery point.)</p><p>To be eligible, a spell must be incapable of targeting more than one creature at the spell’s current circle. For example, <em>magic missile</em> and <em>scorching ray</em> aren’t eligible but <em>acid arrow</em> and <em>ray of enfeeblement</em> are.</p>",
